snippet: David Price struck out five to win his second straight start since returning from an injury, and the Rays beat the White Sox for their eighth victory in nine games.
abstract: Baseball Roundup; Tampa Bay Rays beat Chicago White Sox, 3-1, to cap three-game sweep; other scores noted.
lead_paragraph: David Price struck out five to win his second straight start since returning from an injury, and the Rays beat the White Sox for their eighth victory in nine games.
